postcontent: My Loss is your gain; I purchased This Firearm new in October 17’. It has only been used for one round of trap at my local range. This gun is everything you’d expect from Beretta, its smooth and very well balanced. This gun is an investment that can be passed on for generations; all of the components and functionality to this gun have been designed with the sportsman’s field needs being top priority. The matte finished wood stock and bronze recover will stand out while on display in a gun safe or local trap range. The Barrel sight rib was damaged while it was placed in a holding rack at the trap range. The firearm fell over and landed on the concrete while out of my sight and I had not even fired a round with it yet. It was immediately looked over by a professional gunsmith that happened to be onsite at that time and was determined the damage was isolated to the site rib only and was safe to use. Immediately Beretta USA was contacted with an email and pictures of the damage, after review of information it was sent to Beretta’s factory gunsmith shop Colegunsmithing. This second party specializes in shotguns and is one of only a handful of shops in the United States Authorized to do factory repairs of Beretta Shotguns. The Barrel was fixed and the dents were removed, it was then thoroughly inspected and given a clean bill of health from the team at Cole Gunsmithing. I have all paper work and receipts confirming this work along with all purchase receipts and warrantees. I am willing to provide all stated paperwork on request.
